Autonomous SOP Execution Platform (ASEP)
AI-Powered Enterprise Workflow Orchestration System

Version: 1.0
Project Type: AI Engineering + Enterprise Software + Workflow Automation
Author: Mohamed Shakir

1. Executive Summary

The Autonomous SOP Execution Platform (ASEP) is an AI-powered workflow orchestration system designed to transform static Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) into executable enterprise workflows.

Organizations maintain thousands of SOPs that employees must manually follow to perform operational tasks. This leads to delays, inconsistency, human errors, and increased operational costs.

ASEP addresses this problem by using Artificial Intelligence to:

Understand SOP documents.
Extract workflow logic and business rules.
Generate executable workflow definitions.
Execute workflows autonomously.
Coordinate human approvals when required.
Handle failures and retries.
Maintain workflow state.
Provide monitoring and observability.

The platform initially focuses on Leave Management Workflow Automation as the MVP use case and later expands to domains such as IT Incident Management, Procurement, Compliance, and Invoice Processing.

2. Problem Statement

Most enterprise processes rely on written SOPs.

Examples include:

Leave approvals
Employee onboarding
Invoice approvals
Procurement requests
IT incident handling
Compliance reviews
Vendor management

Current process:

Employee reads SOP
↓
Employee performs actions manually
↓
Manager reviews manually
↓
Systems updated manually
↓
Workflow tracked manually

Challenges:

High operational overhead
Human errors
Slow execution
Lack of visibility
Poor auditability
Difficult process scaling

Existing workflow systems generally require workflows to be manually configured and lack the ability to dynamically understand SOP documents using AI.

3. Project Vision

To build an intelligent enterprise platform capable of:

Understanding procedural documents, generating workflow logic automatically, and autonomously executing business operations with minimal human intervention.

The platform aims to act as a digital workflow operator rather than a simple workflow management system.

